40|$|Repurchase {{agreements}} (repos) are a <b>financing</b> <b>instrument</b> {{widely used}} by holders of debt securities and {{play an important}} role in assisting the smooth functioning of debt markets. Although akin to secured financing, repo rates have recently tended to trade above those on unsecured borrowings. This article outlines the structure of the Australian repo market and considers recent trends in the pricing of repos relative to other short-term interest rates. Repurchase agreement; Repo; Market Operations...|$|E
40|$|The {{main goal}} of this {{bachelor}} thesis is to analyze the use of <b>instruments</b> of housing <b>finance</b> through the financial market and housing policy and its instruments. The first part {{will focus on the}} general characteristics of housing, its peculiarities, classification of forms and <b>financing</b> <b>instruments,</b> focusing on building savings and mortgage lending. The individual objective is to analyze the current product offerings of the Czech financial market intended for housing and a comparison of their main properties. The analytical part will contain model example comparing the conditions and the use of housing <b>finance</b> <b>instruments</b> selected financial institutions in the current period and selection of the most suitable solution for the chosen model situation...|$|R
